W10348269 Dishwasher Circulation Pump Step By Step Instructions As With Any Repair, Be Sure to Turn Off the Power to Your Dishwasher Before Beginning;To Make it Easier to Access the Drain Pump, We Recommend Removing the Outer Door Panel;Remove the Screws from Inside the Door Which Secure the Outer Panel, and Pull the Panel Down then Lift it Up and Out;Now Rotate the Lower Access Panel Fasteners Counter-Clockwise to Remove then Pull Out the Access Panel and Sound Dampening Pad;Reach Under the Dishwasher and Disconnect the Wire Connecter from the Drain Pump, Now Depress the Tab and Rotate the Pump Counter-Clockwise to Remove;Install the New Drain Pump by Inserting It into the Sump Housing and Rotating it Clockwise to Lock it into Place;Connect the Wire Connecter to the New Pump;Reposition the Lower Access Panel and Sound Dampening Pad then Secure the Panel with the Fasteners;Reinstall the Outer Door Panel by First Aligning It on the Door Hinges then Slide the Panel Up and Reinstall the Screws in the Inner Panel to Secure;You’re Now Ready to Restore Power to the Dishwasher and Confirm that it’s Working Properly.

Q & A Q: Having trouble with the dishwasher draining. I replaced the drain pump 30 days ago and it worked fine. Now i have the same issue, it will not drain. It will drain if you "force" it to drain by holding down the start button for 3 seconds, but you have to repeat that 4 times to get it to fully drain. Any thoughts? A: There are a few parts that could cause the issue. It seems like your problem is that it will not drain automatically. I would suggest checking your door latch switches just to make sure they are working. If they are not the machine may think the door is open and will not go into the automatic drain cycle. However, if that part is working then it may be your control board that is the issue. Q: Should the sump be drained completely at the end of the full cycle? When our dishwasher is done there is an inch or so of water in the bottom of the sump. A: The If there is water left over at the end of the cycle, I would suggest checking the water inlet valve to be sure its not leaking into the unit, the float switch and the drain pump itself. Also check the drain hose, to be sure there are no blockages preventing all the water from being pushed out of the unit. Q: Drain pump screaching, working but making noise A: there may be something stuck inside of it, otherwise you can to replace it altogether.
